# Step-7 Freezes The Carried Witness To F_SS(1/12) On The Canonical Packet Ledger

Status: `VERIFIED` Step-7 witness freeze with `INFERRED` downstream carry rule

The completed Step-7 exploration does not keep the friendly family `F_SS(mu)`
open as a live branch parameter.
It freezes the single carried witness `F_SS(1/12)` on the already canonical
one-bridge role-labeled helical packet ledger
`P_n = (A_n, B_n, C_n, D_n, E_n)`,
with `A_n` the active carrier, `B_n` the slow clock, `C_n` the tiny trigger,
`D_n` the transfer conduit / rotor leg, and `E_n = A_{n+1}`.

The carried witness inherits the same packet semantics already frozen earlier:
the desired interaction core
`A -> B`,
`A -> C`,
`B,C -> C`,
`C,A <-> D`,
`D,D -> E`,
the forced spectator classes `mirror`, `companion`, `feedback`, and `cross`,
and packet identity at packet level with mandatory conjugate completion kept
as bookkeeping for real-valuedness rather than as a second witness object.

Its carried sheet is fixed rather than re-optimized:
one role order, one conjugate-representative convention, one helical basis,
one sign sheet, one amplitude anchor, one phase anchor, the normalized window
`I = [0, 1]`, `|A_n(0)| = 1`, `arg A_n(0) = 0`,
`int_I D_on(t) dt = 1`, and the tiny-trigger anchor `|C_n(0)| = 1/128`.

Step 7 therefore carries one exact downstream witness rather than one friendly
family.
Later exact-closure bookkeeping may still record extra modes or companions
only when this same witness forces them on the same ledger, but those
additions count as closure-forced bookkeeping, not as witness replacement or
as a reopening of `mu`.

