+# Step-8 Reconstructs The Raw Classwise Closure Ledger For F_SS(1/12) On The Frozen Witness Sheet
+
+Status: `VERIFIED` inherited witness sheet and class data with `INFERRED` raw closure-ledger synthesis
+
+The local record already supports one raw classwise exact-closure ledger for
+the carried witness `F_SS(1/12)` on the frozen Step-7 packet sheet.
+On the same normalized window `I = [0, 1]`, the desired core burden is
+`Q_clk = 1/6`,
+`Q_seed = 1/12`,
+`Q_amp = 1/4`,
+`Q_rot^D = 1/4`,
+`Q_rot^A = 1/12`,
+`Q_next = 1/6`,
+while the closure-forced spectator burden is
+`mirror = 1/12`,
+`companion = 1/12`,
+`feedback = 1/24`,
+and `cross = 1/24`.
+
+This ledger is inherited rather than invented in Step 8.
+Step 7 already froze the carried witness, canonical packet semantics,
+spectator classes, sign / phase / normalization sheet, and fixed window;
+Step 4 already made the `mu = 1/12` burden values explicit on that witness;
+and Step 2 already fixed that exact Navier-Stokes forces mirror / conjugate,
+same-scale companion, long-leg feedback, and cross-scale next-shell extras
+around the five-channel core.
+
+Step 8 therefore earns one honest closure-burden sheet by interaction class
+on the same frozen ledger.
+What it reconstructs is the classwise raw burden of exact closure, not a new
+mode-by-mode support list.
+
+Filed from:
