+# The Current Record Still Does Not Freeze One Finite Exact Support Closure Ledger For F_SS(1/12)
+
+Status: `VERIFIED` missing support-level closure data with `INFERRED` no-finite-closure verdict
+
+The repository still does not pin one explicit support-level exact-closure
+realization for `F_SS(1/12)`.
+What is missing is not just one citation.
+The local record does not yet freeze one explicit wavevector family for the
+five roles, one helical sign assignment, one exact coefficient ledger
+`C_{k,p,q}^{sigma_k,sigma_p,sigma_q}`, and one finite packet-closure
+convention saying exactly which companion modes must be kept once closure is
+enforced.
+
+The inherited Step-4 branch freeze
+`one primary mode per role + mandatory conjugates + only closure-forced companions`
+is therefore a policy about admissible enlargement, not an enumerated finite
+support list.
+So the current record knows the types of forced additions and their classwise
+totals on the carried witness sheet, but it still does not know one finite
+exact closed subsystem on that same ledger.
+
+Any later finite mode list would need a new wavevector / helicity realization
+choice or a new truncation convention.
+That would be new bookkeeping rather than inherited closure data.
+Step 8 must therefore stop at the classwise closure-burden ledger and may not
+upgrade it into a finite exact support closure claim.
+
+Filed from:
+- `missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/library-inbox/step-008-exploration-001-raw-exact-closure-ledger.md`
